7a5dec8b-da4f-4ef1-8622-e40ddf0e96fd	f963f97f-e03f-4383-bac3-d8849e9a7c71	\N	67	67	How to Build a Diversified Portfolio in 2026	build-diversified-portfolio-2026	A practical framework for spreading risk across asset classes, sectors, and geographies.	https://picsum.photos/seed/build-diversified-portfolio-2026/1200/675	article	[{"id": "b0", "type": "paragraph", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "Diversification remains the closest thing to a free lunch in investing."}}, {"id": "b1", "type": "heading", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "Why diversification works", "level": 2}}, {"id": "b2", "type": "paragraph", "order": 2, "content": {"text": "Combining assets that do not move in lockstep smooths returns and reduces the odds of a catastrophic drawdown."}}, {"id": "b3", "type": "heading", "order": 3, "content": {"text": "A simple model portfolio", "level": 2}}, {"id": "b4", "type": "paragraph", "order": 4, "content": {"text": "A common starting point is a globally diversified mix of equities and bonds, tilted to your time horizon and risk tolerance."}}, {"id": "b5", "type": "callout", "order": 5, "content": {"text": "Rebalance once or twice a year — not every time the market wobbles.", "variant": "info"}}]	[]	{"title": "How to Build a Diversified Portfolio in 2026", "description": "A practical framework for spreading risk across asset classes, sectors, and geographies."}	published	public	2026-05-30 15:23:45.777+00	\N	0	1	{}	2026-05-30 15:23:45.763+00	2026-05-30 15:23:45.782+00	[]
