a77369c2-9da3-454f-8247-92bbf3c95273	cf2d3583-7247-48a6-9fd2-0959043c7a8b	7af8e8d1-cda9-447a-abdf-17b95681b81d	67	67	Infrastructure Layer	eco-infrastructure-layer	The backbone for global business operations.	\N	post	[]	[]	{"title": "Infrastructure Layer", "description": "The backbone for global business operations."}	published	public	2026-05-30 12:03:08.524037+00	\N	0	0	{"kind": "ecosystem", "layer": "Infrastructure", "domain": "baalvionstack.com"}	2026-05-30 11:41:17.645+00	2026-05-30 12:04:31.536828+00	["7af8e8d1-cda9-447a-abdf-17b95681b81d"]
2f1c8817-e163-4f96-bc58-82fd268e9410	cf2d3583-7247-48a6-9fd2-0959043c7a8b	7766576c-0f03-423e-b4fb-aa5d38418634	67	67	Intelligence Layer	eco-intelligence-layer	AI-driven research, analytics, and market insight across the ecosystem.	\N	post	[]	[]	{"title": "Intelligence Layer", "description": "AI-driven research, analytics, and market insight across the ecosystem."}	published	public	2026-05-30 12:03:08.524037+00	\N	0	0	{"kind": "ecosystem", "layer": "Intelligence", "domain": "intel.baalvion.com"}	2026-05-30 11:41:17.65+00	2026-05-30 12:04:31.536828+00	["7766576c-0f03-423e-b4fb-aa5d38418634"]
afa31903-ea61-45ea-b68c-75c85cf11f99	cf2d3583-7247-48a6-9fd2-0959043c7a8b	\N	67	67	A Real-Time Fraud Detection Engine	fraud-detection-engine	Hybrid rules-plus-machine-learning fraud detection for payments at scale — catching fraud in milliseconds without blocking good customers.	https://picsum.photos/seed/cs-fraud/1200/630	event	[{"id": "blk-0", "type": "heading", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "The Challenge", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-1", "type": "paragraph", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "The operator relied on static fraud rules. Tightening them blocked legitimate customers and hurt revenue; loosening them let fraud through. Rules alone couldn't capture the subtle, shifting patterns of real fraud, and scoring happened in batch — by the time fraud was flagged, the money was often gone."}}, {"id": "blk-2", "type": "heading", "order": 2, "content": {"text": "The Solution", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-3", "type": "paragraph", "order": 3, "content": {"text": "We built a hybrid fraud engine on the Baalvion Operating System. Deterministic rules handle clear-cut cases instantly, while a machine-learning model scores the ambiguous majority on signals like velocity, device, and behavioural history. Scoring happens in real time, in the payment path, and analyst decisions feed back to retrain the model — the production-ML discipline described in [building production AI systems](/news/tech/building-production-ai-systems)."}}, {"id": "blk-4", "type": "html", "order": 4, "content": {"html": "<ul><li><strong>Rules overlay</strong> for unambiguous fraud and policy.</li><li><strong>ML scoring</strong> for nuanced, shifting patterns.</li><li><strong>Real-time</strong> scoring inside the payment path.</li><li><strong>Feedback loop</strong> turning analyst decisions into training data.</li></ul>"}}, {"id": "blk-5", "type": "heading", "order": 5, "content": {"text": "Architecture", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-6", "type": "paragraph", "order": 6, "content": {"text": "A feature pipeline computes signals from streaming transaction events. A low-latency scoring service evaluates each payment with the ML model, then a rules overlay applies hard policy. Confirmed-fraud and confirmed-good labels from analysts flow back into the feature store to retrain the model on a schedule — the same feature-and-evaluation rigour we apply across [AI solutions](/services/ai-solutions)."}}, {"id": "blk-7", "type": "heading", "order": 7, "content": {"text": "Technology Stack", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-8", "type": "paragraph", "order": 8, "content": {"text": "A streaming feature pipeline, a real-time ML scoring service, a deterministic rules overlay, and a labelled feedback loop — built through our [AI solutions](/services/ai-solutions) and [automation](/services/automation) practices for the [finance](/industries/finance) sector."}}, {"id": "blk-9", "type": "heading", "order": 9, "content": {"text": "Results", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-10", "type": "paragraph", "order": 10, "content": {"text": "Scoring runs in milliseconds inside the payment path. Fraud caught rose by roughly 34% while false positives fell by 41% — the operator stopped more fraud *and* stopped blocking good customers, because the model captured nuance that static rules never could."}}, {"id": "blk-11", "type": "heading", "order": 11, "content": {"text": "Lessons Learned", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-12", "type": "paragraph", "order": 12, "content": {"text": "Pairing rules with ML gave certainty where it existed and nuance where it didn't. Real-time scoring was essential — batch scoring just documents fraud after the fact. And closing the loop, so analyst decisions retrain the model, kept the engine sharp as fraud patterns evolved."}}]	[]	{"title": "Case Study: Real-Time Fraud Detection Engine | Baalvion", "keywords": ["fraud detection", "payments", "machine learning", "risk scoring", "Baalvion case study", "real-time scoring"], "description": "How Baalvion built a hybrid rules-plus-ML fraud detection engine that scores payments in milliseconds while keeping false positives low."}	published	public	2026-06-11 12:31:30.356+00	\N	12	1	{"faqs": [{"a": "Rules give instant certainty for clear cases and policy; ML captures the subtle, shifting patterns rules miss. Together they catch more fraud with fewer false positives.", "q": "Why combine rules with machine learning?"}, {"a": "Milliseconds, inside the payment path — fraud is evaluated before the transaction completes, not after the fact.", "q": "How fast is scoring?"}, {"a": "Analyst decisions on flagged transactions feed back as labels that retrain the model on a schedule, so it adapts as fraud evolves.", "q": "How does the model stay current?"}, {"a": "By scoring nuance rather than blunt thresholds, the engine cut false positives by 41%, reducing wrongly blocked legitimate payments.", "q": "How are good customers protected?"}], "kind": "case_study", "client": "A high-volume payments operator on the Baalvion ledger", "sector": "Finance", "lessons": ["Combine rules for certainty with ML for nuance.", "Score in real time or you're reviewing history.", "Close the loop: analyst decisions retrain the model."], "results": [{"value": "Milliseconds", "metric": "Scoring latency"}, {"value": "+34%", "metric": "Fraud caught"}, {"value": "-41%", "metric": "False positives"}], "solution": "A hybrid engine combining deterministic rules with ML scoring and a feedback loop.", "challenge": "Static rules were either too loose (missed fraud) or too tight (blocked good customers).", "techStack": ["Feature pipeline", "ML scoring", "Rules overlay", "Streaming events", "Feedback loop"], "architecture": "Feature pipeline, real-time scoring service, rules overlay, analyst feedback loop.", "internalLinks": [{"href": "/news/tech/building-production-ai-systems", "anchor": "building production AI systems"}, {"href": "/services/ai-solutions", "anchor": "AI solutions"}, {"href": "/services/automation", "anchor": "automation"}, {"href": "/industries/finance", "anchor": "finance"}]}	2026-06-11 12:31:29.939+00	2026-06-19 08:41:11.379+00	[]
c72b49b1-589a-4fac-bf59-95b105854f1c	7bced69e-a861-4530-9660-e0ddb955d72b	10856fbd-44fe-4175-8af6-f69faf6a93b7	67	67	Deepak Kumar Kuldeep	deepak-kumar-kuldeep	Founder & Chief Visionary Officer	\N	post	[{"id": "blk-bio", "type": "paragraph", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "<p>Deepak Kumar Kuldeep is the Founder and Chief Visionary Officer of Baalvion Industries Private Limited. Deepak founded the company with a vision to build a unified, technology-led operating system for global B2B trade and industrial commerce, and continues to set its long-term direction, culture and innovation agenda.</p><h2>Focus areas</h2><ul><li>Long-term vision and company strategy</li><li>Innovation and new business opportunities</li><li>Culture, values and leadership</li><li>Partnerships and global expansion</li></ul><p>As Founder, Deepak guides Baalvion Industries' mission to modernise global trade through scalable digital infrastructure, intelligent systems and a relentless focus on long-term value creation.</p>"}}]	[]	{"title": "Deepak Kumar Kuldeep", "description": "Deepak is the driving force behind Baalvion, bringing over two decades of experience in global trade and technology. His vision is to build a transparent and efficient ecosystem for B2B commerce worldwide."}	published	public	2026-06-07 01:15:42.782+00	\N	8	1	{"kind": "leadership", "role": "Founder & Chief Visionary Officer", "tier": "executive-committee", "order": 0, "imageId": "founder-photo"}	2026-06-07 01:15:42.292+00	2026-06-07 18:54:05.53+00	["10856fbd-44fe-4175-8af6-f69faf6a93b7"]
b0ef123b-48ff-47a4-a672-7eb57b219229	f963f97f-e03f-4383-bac3-d8849e9a7c71	de367c96-506d-4094-bb14-c969245307e8	9000099	9000099	How to Choose a Checking Account With No Hidden Fees	checking-account-no-hidden-fees	Monthly maintenance, overdraft, and ATM fees quietly erode your balance. A simple checklist to avoid them.	https://picsum.photos/seed/checking/1200/675	article	[{"id": "b0", "type": "paragraph", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "Not all checking accounts are created equal. The cheapest headline can hide costly fees."}}, {"id": "b1", "type": "paragraph", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "Look for accounts that waive monthly maintenance fees with direct deposit, reimburse out-of-network ATM charges, and offer fee-free overdraft protection."}}, {"id": "b2", "type": "paragraph", "order": 2, "content": {"text": "Credit unions and online-only banks often beat large national banks on total cost of ownership."}}]	[]	{"title": "How to Choose a Checking Account With No Hidden Fees", "description": "Monthly maintenance, overdraft, and ATM fees quietly erode your balance. A simple checklist to avoid them."}	published	public	2026-06-07 07:40:05.755+00	\N	0	1	{}	2026-06-07 07:40:05.742+00	2026-06-07 07:41:23.876+00	["de367c96-506d-4094-bb14-c969245307e8"]
957436b3-ca45-4fea-8b01-354418b9d8ef	99560d59-8370-4d7f-b451-d4a7edab85a8	df6284f9-c021-488f-8b97-85032b1e3b68	67	67	Drafting Enforceable Commercial Contracts: A Complete Guide	drafting-enforceable-commercial-contracts	A practical, end-to-end guide to the clauses, structure, and review process that make a commercial contract enforceable and dispute-resistant.	\N	article	[{"id": "blk-0", "type": "paragraph", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "A commercial contract is more than a record of a deal — it is the operating manual for a business relationship and the script the parties will follow if that relationship breaks down. A well-drafted agreement allocates risk clearly, defines what each side must do, and sets out exactly what happens when something goes wrong. A poorly drafted one invites disputes, erodes margins, and can be unenforceable precisely when you need it most. This guide walks through the anatomy of an enforceable commercial contract and the drafting discipline that keeps it strong."}}, {"id": "blk-1", "type": "html", "order": 1, "content": {"html": "<div class=\\"key-takeaways\\"><h4>Key Takeaways</h4><ul><li>Enforceability rests on offer, acceptance, consideration, certainty of terms, and intention to create legal relations.</li><li>The most litigated clauses are scope, payment, termination, limitation of liability, and dispute resolution.</li><li>Plain, specific drafting beats dense boilerplate — ambiguity is construed against the drafter.</li><li>A short pre-signature review checklist prevents most expensive contract disputes.</li></ul></div>"}}, {"id": "blk-2", "type": "heading", "order": 2, "content": {"text": "What Makes a Contract Legally Enforceable", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-3", "type": "paragraph", "order": 3, "content": {"text": "Before worrying about individual clauses, a contract has to clear the basic threshold of formation. Courts generally look for five things: a clear offer, an unqualified acceptance of that offer, consideration (something of value exchanged by each side), certainty of terms, and an intention by both parties to be legally bound. Commercial agreements between businesses almost always satisfy the intention requirement, but the other elements are where drafting matters. If essential terms — price, quantity, duration, deliverables — are vague or left \\"to be agreed later,\\" a court may find there was never a binding contract at all."}}, {"id": "blk-4", "type": "paragraph", "order": 4, "content": {"text": "Capacity and legality round out the picture. Each signatory must have authority to bind their organisation, and the contract's purpose must be lawful. A surprising number of disputes turn on whether the person who signed actually had authority to do so, which is why well-run businesses keep a clear signing matrix and ask for evidence of authority on significant deals."}}, {"id": "blk-5", "type": "heading", "order": 5, "content": {"text": "The Core Clauses Every Commercial Contract Needs", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-6", "type": "paragraph", "order": 6, "content": {"text": "Most commercial contracts share a common skeleton. Understanding what each part is for helps you spot what is missing and what is doing real work versus what is filler."}}, {"id": "blk-7", "type": "heading", "order": 7, "content": {"text": "Scope and Deliverables", "level": 3}}, {"id": "blk-8", "type": "paragraph", "order": 8, "content": {"text": "This is the heart of the agreement: what exactly is being supplied, to what standard, and by when. Vague scope is the single biggest source of commercial disputes. Wherever possible, define deliverables with measurable acceptance criteria, attach detailed specifications as a schedule, and state expressly what is out of scope. A clause that says \\"the supplier will provide consulting services\\" is an argument waiting to happen; one that lists named deliverables, milestones, and acceptance tests is not."}}, {"id": "blk-9", "type": "heading", "order": 9, "content": {"text": "Payment and Consideration", "level": 3}}, {"id": "blk-10", "type": "paragraph", "order": 10, "content": {"text": "Spell out the amount, currency, timing, invoicing mechanics, and what triggers payment. Address late payment with interest and suspension rights, and clarify whether prices are inclusive or exclusive of tax. If payment depends on milestones or acceptance, tie the two clauses together explicitly so there is no gap between \\"work delivered\\" and \\"payment due.\\""}}, {"id": "blk-11", "type": "heading", "order": 11, "content": {"text": "Term, Renewal, and Termination", "level": 3}}, {"id": "blk-12", "type": "paragraph", "order": 12, "content": {"text": "State when the contract starts, how long it runs, and how it renews. Termination provisions should distinguish termination for convenience (with notice) from termination for cause (material breach, insolvency, change of control). Define what counts as a material breach and give a cure period where appropriate. Just as important, set out the consequences of termination: final payments, return of property, survival of confidentiality, and transition assistance."}}, {"id": "blk-13", "type": "heading", "order": 13, "content": {"text": "Limitation of Liability and Indemnities", "level": 3}}, {"id": "blk-14", "type": "paragraph", "order": 14, "content": {"text": "These clauses decide who carries the financial risk when things go wrong, and they are heavily negotiated for good reason. A limitation clause typically caps total liability (often by reference to fees paid) and excludes certain categories of loss such as indirect or consequential damages. Indemnities shift responsibility for specific risks — third-party IP claims, data breaches, personal injury — to the party best able to control them. Courts scrutinise these clauses closely, so they must be clear, reasonable, and not attempt to exclude liability the law does not allow to be excluded."}}, {"id": "blk-15", "type": "heading", "order": 15, "content": {"text": "The Clauses People Forget — Until They Need Them", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-16", "type": "paragraph", "order": 16, "content": {"text": "Beyond the headline terms, a set of \\"boilerplate\\" clauses quietly determines how the contract behaves under stress. They are not filler:"}}, {"id": "blk-17", "type": "html", "order": 17, "content": {"html": "<ul><li><strong>Governing law and jurisdiction</strong> — which country's law applies and which courts hear disputes. Essential in any cross-border deal.</li><li><strong>Dispute resolution</strong> — whether disputes go to litigation, arbitration, or a tiered process of negotiation then mediation then arbitration.</li><li><strong>Force majeure</strong> — what happens when events outside either party's control prevent performance.</li><li><strong>Confidentiality</strong> — protecting sensitive information shared during the relationship, surviving termination.</li><li><strong>Assignment and subcontracting</strong> — whether either party can transfer its rights or delegate its obligations.</li><li><strong>Entire agreement and variation</strong> — confirming the written contract is the whole deal and can only be changed in writing.</li><li><strong>Notices</strong> — how formal communications must be delivered to be valid.</li></ul>"}}, {"id": "blk-18", "type": "heading", "order": 18, "content": {"text": "Drafting Style: Clarity Is Enforceability", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-19", "type": "paragraph", "order": 19, "content": {"text": "The way a contract is written affects whether it holds up. Use short sentences and defined terms consistently. Where a word has a specific meaning, define it once and capitalise it throughout. Avoid stacking synonyms (\\"null, void and of no effect\\") that add nothing but ambiguity. Number clauses logically and keep related provisions together. Remember the contra proferentem principle: where a clause is genuinely ambiguous, courts often construe it against the party that drafted it. Precision is not pedantry — it is risk management."}}, {"id": "blk-20", "type": "paragraph", "order": 20, "content": {"text": "Schedules and annexes are your friend. Keep the main body focused on legal mechanics and push detailed specifications, pricing tables, and service levels into clearly referenced schedules. This keeps the contract readable and makes future amendments cleaner."}}, {"id": "blk-21", "type": "heading", "order": 21, "content": {"text": "A Pre-Signature Review Checklist", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-22", "type": "paragraph", "order": 22, "content": {"text": "Before any commercial contract is signed, run it through a short, disciplined review. Most expensive disputes trace back to a step skipped here:"}}, {"id": "blk-23", "type": "html", "order": 23, "content": {"html": "<ul><li>Are the parties correctly named, with the right legal entities and signing authority confirmed?</li><li>Is the scope specific, measurable, and matched to the commercial deal that was actually agreed?</li><li>Do payment triggers align with delivery and acceptance, with late-payment remedies?</li><li>Are termination rights, notice periods, and post-termination obligations clear and balanced?</li><li>Is the liability cap commercially sensible, and are the indemnities reciprocal where appropriate?</li><li>Do the governing law, jurisdiction, and dispute-resolution clauses fit where the parties actually operate?</li><li>Have all referenced schedules and annexes been attached and checked?</li></ul>"}}, {"id": "blk-24", "type": "heading", "order": 24, "content": {"text": "Frequently Asked Questions", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-25", "type": "heading", "order": 25, "content": {"text": "Does a contract have to be in writing to be enforceable?", "level": 3}}, {"id": "blk-26", "type": "paragraph", "order": 26, "content": {"text": "Many oral contracts are enforceable, but certain categories — such as those involving land or guarantees — usually must be in writing. Even where an oral contract is valid, proving its terms is difficult. For any commercial relationship of substance, a written agreement is strongly preferable because it records exactly what was agreed."}}, {"id": "blk-27", "type": "heading", "order": 27, "content": {"text": "What is the difference between a warranty and an indemnity?", "level": 3}}, {"id": "blk-28", "type": "paragraph", "order": 28, "content": {"text": "A warranty is a contractual promise that a fact is true; if it is breached, the innocent party claims damages and must prove its loss. An indemnity is a promise to reimburse a defined loss directly, often without the usual rules on proving and limiting damages, which is why indemnities are negotiated carefully."}}, {"id": "blk-29", "type": "heading", "order": 29, "content": {"text": "Can we just use a template we found online?", "level": 3}}, {"id": "blk-30", "type": "paragraph", "order": 30, "content": {"text": "Templates can be a useful starting point, but they are written for a generic situation and a particular jurisdiction. Using one unaltered risks missing terms specific to your deal, including clauses that do not apply, or relying on language that is unenforceable where you operate. Treat templates as a checklist, not a finished contract."}}, {"id": "blk-31", "type": "heading", "order": 31, "content": {"text": "Conclusion", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-32", "type": "paragraph", "order": 32, "content": {"text": "An enforceable commercial contract is built, not copied. It starts from the commercial reality of the deal, expresses each party's obligations with precision, allocates risk deliberately, and plans for the relationship ending as carefully as it plans for it succeeding. Invest in clear scope, sensible liability terms, and a workable dispute-resolution path, and the contract becomes what it should be: a tool that prevents disputes far more often than it resolves them."}}, {"id": "blk-33", "type": "html", "order": 33, "content": {"html": "<p><em>This article is general legal information, not legal advice. Laws vary by jurisdiction and change over time. Consult a qualified practitioner about your specific situation.</em></p>"}}]	[]	{"title": "Drafting Enforceable Commercial Contracts: A Complete Guide | Law Elite", "keywords": ["commercial contract", "contract drafting", "enforceable contract", "business agreement", "contract clauses"], "description": "Learn the essential clauses, structure, and review steps that make a commercial contract enforceable and ready to survive a dispute."}	published	public	2026-06-10 14:46:44.071+00	\N	3	1	{"kind": "article", "tags": ["contracts", "corporate", "drafting", "commercial-law"], "alphabet": "D", "featured": true, "readingTime": "8 min read"}	2026-06-10 14:46:43.72+00	2026-06-10 16:20:54.425+00	["df6284f9-c021-488f-8b97-85032b1e3b68"]
fe2c66bf-a653-4734-80ad-70cef6c0e236	f963f97f-e03f-4383-bac3-d8849e9a7c71	1c5830d6-5401-4573-b6bb-bbd50192d788	67	67	The Baalvion Empire	the-baalvion-empire	A comprehensive overview of the Baalvion Empire, its origins, and global reach.	\N	article	[{"id": "blk-0", "type": "heading", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "Origins", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-1", "type": "paragraph", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "The Baalvion Empire emerged as a federated network of digital and physical enterprises spanning commerce, media, mining, and law."}}, {"id": "blk-2", "type": "paragraph", "order": 2, "content": {"text": "Its governance model is built on a centralized identity and a multi-tenant operating system."}}]	[]	{"title": "The Baalvion Empire", "description": "A comprehensive overview of the Baalvion Empire, its origins, and global reach."}	published	public	2026-05-30 12:03:31.55413+00	\N	2	1	{}	2026-05-29 22:14:29.56+00	2026-05-30 12:06:36.325+00	["1c5830d6-5401-4573-b6bb-bbd50192d788"]
0ecd33e8-4390-4519-b6e7-d8f3c2e9cb00	f963f97f-e03f-4383-bac3-d8849e9a7c71	\N	67	67	Understanding Index Funds and ETFs	understanding-index-funds-etfs	Low-cost, passive vehicles that have reshaped how people invest.	https://picsum.photos/seed/understanding-index-funds-etfs/1200/675	article	[{"id": "b0", "type": "paragraph", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "Index funds track a benchmark instead of trying to beat it."}}, {"id": "b1", "type": "heading", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "Funds vs. ETFs", "level": 2}}, {"id": "b2", "type": "paragraph", "order": 2, "content": {"text": "Both can track the same index; ETFs trade intraday like stocks while mutual funds price once a day."}}, {"id": "b3", "type": "heading", "order": 3, "content": {"text": "Why costs matter", "level": 2}}, {"id": "b4", "type": "paragraph", "order": 4, "content": {"text": "Over decades, a 0.5% fee difference can cost you tens of thousands of dollars in compounded returns."}}, {"id": "b5", "type": "callout", "order": 5, "content": {"text": "For most investors, a low-cost total-market index fund is a sensible core holding.", "variant": "info"}}]	[]	{"title": "Understanding Index Funds and ETFs", "description": "Low-cost, passive vehicles that have reshaped how people invest."}	published	public	2026-05-30 15:23:45.796+00	\N	0	1	{}	2026-05-30 15:23:45.79+00	2026-05-30 15:23:45.799+00	[]
9ec38055-fe26-469b-84d0-9f86f69ffb2c	f963f97f-e03f-4383-bac3-d8849e9a7c71	\N	67	67	A Beginner Guide to Bonds	beginner-guide-to-bonds	How fixed-income works and where it fits in a portfolio.	https://picsum.photos/seed/beginner-guide-to-bonds/1200/675	article	[{"id": "b0", "type": "paragraph", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "A bond is a loan you make to a government or company in exchange for interest."}}, {"id": "b1", "type": "heading", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "Yields and prices", "level": 2}}, {"id": "b2", "type": "paragraph", "order": 2, "content": {"text": "Bond prices move inversely to interest rates — when rates rise, existing bond prices fall."}}, {"id": "b3", "type": "heading", "order": 3, "content": {"text": "Duration and risk", "level": 2}}, {"id": "b4", "type": "paragraph", "order": 4, "content": {"text": "Longer-duration bonds are more sensitive to rate changes; short-duration bonds are steadier."}}, {"id": "b5", "type": "callout", "order": 5, "content": {"text": "Bonds cushion a portfolio when equities sell off — that is their job.", "variant": "info"}}]	[]	{"title": "A Beginner Guide to Bonds", "description": "How fixed-income works and where it fits in a portfolio."}	published	public	2026-05-30 15:23:45.828+00	\N	0	1	{}	2026-05-30 15:23:45.823+00	2026-05-30 15:23:45.832+00	[]
968838c7-e49a-4416-8604-cd8cc974b2a2	f963f97f-e03f-4383-bac3-d8849e9a7c71	\N	67	67	Imperialpedia Platform Overview	imperialpedia-platform-overview	Editorial content authored in the Baalvion admin platform now publishes straight to the Imperialpedia website through a single multi-site CMS.	https://picsum.photos/seed/baalvion-cms-news/1200/675	page	[{"id": "b0", "type": "paragraph", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "Baalvion today flipped on a unified content pipeline that lets editors publish to the Imperialpedia knowledge site directly from the central admin platform, with no engineering hand-off."}}, {"id": "b1", "type": "heading", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "One console, many sites", "level": 2}}, {"id": "b2", "type": "paragraph", "order": 2, "content": {"text": "Imperialpedia is registered as a website inside the shared CMS. Articles and news authored there flow through a draft → review → publish workflow and appear on the public site the moment they go live."}}, {"id": "b3", "type": "quote", "order": 3, "content": {"cite": "Baalvion Platform Team", "text": "Publishing should be a button, not a deploy. That is exactly what this delivers."}}, {"id": "b4", "type": "callout", "order": 4, "content": {"text": "Structured data (companies, markets, calculators) stays in the dedicated imperialpedia-service; the CMS owns the editorial layer.", "variant": "info"}}, {"id": "b5", "type": "paragraph", "order": 5, "content": {"text": "The same pipeline is being rolled out across the rest of the Baalvion network of sites."}}]	[]	{"title": "Baalvion Launches Unified Imperialpedia CMS Pipeline", "description": "How Baalvion publishes editorial content to Imperialpedia from one console."}	published	public	2026-05-30 12:34:24.993+00	\N	2	1	{}	2026-05-30 12:34:23.723+00	2026-06-19 22:20:02.629+00	[]
