b79bad23-6444-41bb-b7da-5756deab20bd	d1afcbbb-1ffd-447f-aee7-61d090f78a6b	1	The Collector’s Guide to the Hermès Birkin	{"slug": "guide-hermes-birkin", "title": "The Collector’s Guide to the Hermès Birkin", "status": "published", "tagIds": [], "excerpt": "How to identify, value and acquire the most coveted handbag in the world.", "seoMetadata": {"title": "The Collector’s Guide to the Hermès Birkin", "description": "How to identify, value and acquire the most coveted handbag in the world."}, "customFields": {"date": "2024-03-10", "kind": "buying-guide", "tips": ["Verify the blind-stamp date code and the artisan’s mark.", "Understand leather grades — Togo, Clemence and exotic skins carry different value trajectories.", "Prioritise hardware condition and corner wear over age alone."], "author": "Elena Vance", "category": "Artisanal", "targetKeyword": "hermes birkin buying guide", "investmentOutlook": "Steady 12–15% annual appreciation observed over the last decade for pristine examples."}, "contentBlocks": [{"id": "blk-0", "type": "paragraph", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "The Birkin is not merely a handbag; it is a portable asset class. Acquiring one of magnitude requires intelligence as much as means."}}, {"id": "blk-1", "type": "paragraph", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "Provenance, materiality and condition determine value. A pristine 25cm in a rare leather can outperform far larger pieces."}}]}	67	State changed to published	2026-06-10 19:08:01.491+00
4a061c7c-a06c-42ad-8209-17766df616fd	e4af01b5-e943-4163-9c12-bc7bd138b73e	1	Technology Consulting	{"slug": "technology-consulting", "title": "Technology Consulting", "status": "published", "tagIds": [], "excerpt": "Architecture, modernization, and technology strategy from a team that builds and operates platforms — advice grounded in production reality.", "seoMetadata": {"title": "Technology Consulting & Architecture | Baalvion", "keywords": ["technology consulting", "architecture review", "technology strategy", "modernization", "Baalvion services", "CTO advisory"], "description": "Baalvion provides technology strategy, architecture review, and modernization consulting grounded in operating real platforms — not slideware."}, "customFields": {"faqs": [{"a": "Scalability, security, reliability, cost, and maintainability of your current architecture — with prioritised, actionable findings rather than a generic checklist.", "q": "What does an architecture review cover?"}, {"a": "Both. We can hand over a plan your team executes, or deliver it with you through our engineering practices.", "q": "Do you only advise, or also build?"}, {"a": "Yes — we weigh cost, control, time-to-value, and lock-in with you. See [custom software vs SaaS](/news/insights/custom-software-vs-saas).", "q": "Can you help with build-vs-buy decisions?"}, {"a": "Yes — for investors or acquirers, we assess architecture, risk, team, and scalability of a target's technology.", "q": "Do you do technical due diligence?"}], "kind": "service", "process": [{"desc": "Understand goals, constraints, and the current estate.", "step": "Listen"}, {"desc": "Architecture, risks, costs, and team capability.", "step": "Assess"}, {"desc": "A prioritised, pragmatic roadmap — not a wish list.", "step": "Recommend"}, {"desc": "Help execute, or hand over a plan your team can run.", "step": "Support"}], "benefits": ["Strategy grounded in operating real systems", "Architecture reviews that find real risk", "Pragmatic modernization roadmaps", "Stack and build-vs-buy decisions made with you"], "techStack": ["Architecture review", "Modernization roadmaps", "Stack selection", "Build-vs-buy analysis", "Due diligence", "Mentoring"], "internalLinks": [{"href": "/platform", "anchor": "Baalvion Operating System"}, {"href": "/news/insights/enterprise-modernization", "anchor": "enterprise modernization"}, {"href": "/news/tech/choosing-the-right-technology-stack", "anchor": "choosing the right technology stack"}, {"href": "/services/custom-software-development", "anchor": "custom software development"}]}, "contentBlocks": [{"id": "blk-0", "type": "heading", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "Overview", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-1", "type": "paragraph", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "The best technology advice comes from people who still build and operate systems. Baalvion's consulting is grounded in running the [Baalvion Operating System](/platform) at scale, so our recommendations account for the realities of production — cost, reliability, team capability, and change over time. We help you choose, modernise, and scale without the abstraction that plagues slide-deck consulting."}}, {"id": "blk-2", "type": "heading", "order": 2, "content": {"text": "Benefits", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-3", "type": "html", "order": 3, "content": {"html": "<ul><li><strong>Grounded:</strong> advice from a team that operates what it recommends.</li><li><strong>Honest architecture reviews</strong> that surface real risk, not theatre.</li><li><strong>Pragmatic roadmaps</strong> prioritised by value and risk.</li><li><strong>Clear decisions:</strong> stack and build-vs-buy made with evidence.</li></ul>"}}, {"id": "blk-4", "type": "heading", "order": 4, "content": {"text": "Our Process", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-5", "type": "paragraph", "order": 5, "content": {"text": "We listen to your goals and constraints, assess your architecture, risks, and team capability, recommend a prioritised roadmap, and then either help execute or hand over a plan your team can own. For modernization-heavy engagements we draw on [enterprise modernization](/news/insights/enterprise-modernization) and the [digital transformation guide](/news/insights/digital-transformation-guide)."}}, {"id": "blk-6", "type": "heading", "order": 6, "content": {"text": "Technologies", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-7", "type": "paragraph", "order": 7, "content": {"text": "Architecture and security reviews, modernization roadmaps, stack selection, build-vs-buy analysis, technical due diligence, and team mentoring. Where execution follows, we bring our [custom software development](/services/custom-software-development), [cloud solutions](/services/cloud-solutions), and [DevOps](/services/devops) practices."}}, {"id": "blk-8", "type": "heading", "order": 8, "content": {"text": "Why Baalvion", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-9", "type": "paragraph", "order": 9, "content": {"text": "We've made these decisions for our own platform and lived with the consequences, which keeps our advice honest. See the thinking in [choosing the right technology stack](/news/tech/choosing-the-right-technology-stack) and [scaling engineering teams](/news/insights/scaling-engineering-teams)."}}]}	67	State changed to published	2026-06-11 12:31:30.166+00
f63c455a-3e36-4a6a-814b-bdf7148ace2a	2ffd2775-8424-42d3-a602-89969fc98e0d	1	Web Development	{"slug": "web-development", "title": "Web Development", "status": "published", "tagIds": [], "excerpt": "Fast, accessible, server-rendered web platforms engineered for Core Web Vitals, SEO, and scale.", "seoMetadata": {"title": "Web Development Services | Baalvion", "keywords": ["web development", "Next.js", "server-side rendering", "Core Web Vitals", "Baalvion services", "web performance"], "description": "Baalvion builds high-performance, server-rendered web platforms engineered for Core Web Vitals, accessibility, SEO, and scale. Explore our process and stack."}, "customFields": {"faqs": [{"a": "SSR gives fast first paint, clean indexability for SEO, and resilience. Combined with static generation and ISR, you get speed and freshness without rebuilds.", "q": "Why server-side rendering?"}, {"a": "Performance budgets, edge caching, code splitting, and real-user monitoring — covered in [web performance optimization](/news/tech/web-performance-optimization).", "q": "How do you keep sites fast as they grow?"}, {"a": "Yes. WCAG-aligned semantics, keyboard navigation, and contrast are built in by default, not added later.", "q": "Is accessibility included?"}, {"a": "We favour Next.js and React with TypeScript, but choose based on your team and goals.", "q": "Which frameworks do you use?"}], "kind": "service", "process": [{"desc": "Audience, goals, and the metrics that matter (CWV, conversion, SEO).", "step": "Define"}, {"desc": "Intentional UI with a real design system, not a template.", "step": "Design"}, {"desc": "Server-rendered, accessible, instrumented for performance.", "step": "Build"}, {"desc": "Lighthouse, real-user metrics, and iteration.", "step": "Measure"}], "benefits": ["Fast first paint and strong Core Web Vitals", "Server-rendered for SEO and resilience", "Accessible by default (WCAG-aligned)", "Built to scale to high traffic"], "techStack": ["Next.js", "React", "TypeScript", "Tailwind CSS", "Edge/CDN", "ISR & SSG"], "internalLinks": [{"href": "/news/tech/web-performance-optimization", "anchor": "web performance optimization"}, {"href": "/news/tech/choosing-the-right-technology-stack", "anchor": "choosing the right technology stack"}, {"href": "/case-studies/luxury-commerce-marketplace", "anchor": "launching a verified luxury commerce marketplace"}, {"href": "/services/cloud-solutions", "anchor": "cloud solutions"}]}, "contentBlocks": [{"id": "blk-0", "type": "heading", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "Overview", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-1", "type": "paragraph", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "A web platform is often the first thing a customer experiences — and the slowest part of most stacks. Baalvion builds web platforms that are fast, accessible, and engineered for search. We default to server rendering for clean indexability and resilience, and we treat performance as a budget, not an afterthought. This very site is built the way we build for clients."}}, {"id": "blk-2", "type": "heading", "order": 2, "content": {"text": "Benefits", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-3", "type": "html", "order": 3, "content": {"html": "<ul><li><strong>Speed:</strong> strong Core Web Vitals through server rendering, caching, and disciplined bundles.</li><li><strong>Discoverability:</strong> SSR/SSG/ISR and structured data for SEO — see <a href=\\"/news/tech/web-performance-optimization\\">web performance optimization</a>.</li><li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> WCAG-aligned semantics and keyboard support by default.</li><li><strong>Scale:</strong> edge caching and incremental rendering for high traffic.</li></ul>"}}, {"id": "blk-4", "type": "heading", "order": 4, "content": {"text": "Our Process", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-5", "type": "paragraph", "order": 5, "content": {"text": "We define the metrics that matter, design an intentional interface with a real design system, build it server-rendered and instrumented, then measure with Lighthouse and real-user data and iterate. Performance and accessibility are acceptance criteria, not nice-to-haves."}}, {"id": "blk-6", "type": "heading", "order": 6, "content": {"text": "Technologies", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-7", "type": "paragraph", "order": 7, "content": {"text": "Next.js and React with TypeScript, Tailwind for a disciplined design system, edge/CDN delivery, and incremental static regeneration for content that stays fresh without rebuilds. The stack choice always follows the goals — see [choosing the right technology stack](/news/tech/choosing-the-right-technology-stack)."}}, {"id": "blk-8", "type": "heading", "order": 8, "content": {"text": "Why Baalvion", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-9", "type": "paragraph", "order": 9, "content": {"text": "We run high-traffic, content-rich web properties across our ecosystem, so we know what breaks at scale and how to avoid it. See the storefront work in [launching a verified luxury commerce marketplace](/case-studies/luxury-commerce-marketplace), and pair this with [cloud solutions](/services/cloud-solutions) and [technology consulting](/services/technology-consulting)."}}]}	67	State changed to published	2026-06-11 12:31:30.183+00
b5862dd3-f929-4c16-9f17-f6144002a1c8	cec88301-a304-49e2-bc32-eea782e39fe5	1	Baalvion for Education	{"slug": "education", "title": "Baalvion for Education", "status": "published", "tagIds": [], "excerpt": "Scalable learning and credentialing platforms — handling peak load, protecting learner data, and integrating cleanly.", "seoMetadata": {"title": "Education Technology Solutions | Baalvion", "keywords": ["education technology", "edtech", "learning platform", "credentialing", "Baalvion industries", "LMS"], "description": "Baalvion builds education platforms that scale through demand peaks, protect learner data, support verifiable credentials, and integrate with existing systems."}, "customFields": {"faqs": [{"a": "Autoscaling, cloud-native architecture and caching absorb sudden surges, so the platform stays responsive when the whole user base arrives at once.", "q": "How do you handle exam-day and enrolment spikes?"}, {"a": "Encryption, least-privilege access, and audit logging — the controls in [secure software development](/news/tech/secure-software-development) — with particular care where minors are involved.", "q": "How is learner data protected?"}, {"a": "Yes — we use append-only, tamper-evident records so certificates and achievements can be independently verified.", "q": "Can credentials be verified?"}, {"a": "Typically [web development](/services/web-development), [cloud solutions](/services/cloud-solutions), and [custom software development](/services/custom-software-development).", "q": "Which services apply to education?"}], "kind": "industry", "solutions": ["Autoscaling infrastructure for demand peaks", "Strong data protection and access control", "Verifiable, tamper-evident credential records", "API-first integration with institutional systems"], "challenges": ["Spiky load around enrolment, exams, and deadlines", "Protecting learner data and privacy", "Trustworthy, verifiable credentials", "Integrating with existing institutional systems"], "internalLinks": [{"href": "/news/tech/cloud-native-architecture", "anchor": "cloud-native architecture"}, {"href": "/news/tech/secure-software-development", "anchor": "secure software development"}, {"href": "/services/web-development", "anchor": "web development"}, {"href": "/news/tech/api-first-architecture", "anchor": "API-first architecture"}]}, "contentBlocks": [{"id": "blk-0", "type": "heading", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "Sector Overview", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-1", "type": "paragraph", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "Education technology faces a distinctive pattern: long quiet periods punctuated by intense spikes — enrolment windows, exam days, assignment deadlines — when the whole user base arrives at once. Add sensitive learner data and the need for credentials people can trust, and you have a demanding engineering problem. Baalvion builds learning platforms that handle all of it."}}, {"id": "blk-2", "type": "heading", "order": 2, "content": {"text": "Challenges", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-3", "type": "html", "order": 3, "content": {"html": "<ul><li><strong>Spiky load:</strong> platforms must absorb sudden, predictable surges.</li><li><strong>Data privacy:</strong> learner data, often including minors, must be protected.</li><li><strong>Credentials:</strong> certificates and records must be verifiable and tamper-evident.</li><li><strong>Integration:</strong> edtech rarely lives alone — it must connect to existing systems.</li></ul>"}}, {"id": "blk-4", "type": "heading", "order": 4, "content": {"text": "How Baalvion Helps", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-5", "type": "paragraph", "order": 5, "content": {"text": "We build on autoscaling [cloud-native architecture](/news/tech/cloud-native-architecture) that absorbs demand peaks without falling over, protect learner data with the controls from [secure software development](/news/tech/secure-software-development), and use append-only records for tamper-evident credentials. Everything integrates the [API-first](/news/tech/api-first-architecture) way with institutional systems."}}, {"id": "blk-6", "type": "heading", "order": 6, "content": {"text": "Relevant Services", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-7", "type": "paragraph", "order": 7, "content": {"text": "Education engagements combine [web development](/services/web-development), [cloud solutions](/services/cloud-solutions), and [custom software development](/services/custom-software-development), with [AI solutions](/services/ai-solutions) for personalisation where it genuinely helps learners."}}, {"id": "blk-8", "type": "heading", "order": 8, "content": {"text": "Outcomes", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-9", "type": "paragraph", "order": 9, "content": {"text": "Education platforms that stay fast and available through every peak, keep learner data safe, issue credentials people can verify, and slot cleanly into the institutional landscape."}}]}	67	State changed to published	2026-06-11 12:31:30.198+00
b3caf1e6-a31d-497b-89af-94d5c8556c22	fe73be1c-81c2-4242-b55f-9bbd56d3343a	1	Baalvion for Finance	{"slug": "finance", "title": "Baalvion for Finance", "status": "published", "tagIds": [], "excerpt": "Trade finance, payments, compliance, and settlement — built on a double-entry ledger with real-time risk screening.", "seoMetadata": {"title": "Financial Technology Solutions | Baalvion", "keywords": ["financial technology", "trade finance", "payments", "settlement", "compliance", "Baalvion industries", "fintech"], "description": "Baalvion builds finance platforms with double-entry ledgering, real-time settlement, and AI compliance screening across 180+ jurisdictions."}, "customFields": {"faqs": [{"a": "It guarantees that every movement balances, making reconciliation and dispute resolution fast and trustworthy — the foundation of any serious finance platform.", "q": "Why a double-entry ledger?"}, {"a": "Real-time AI screening over versioned sanctions data with auditable decisions across 180+ jurisdictions — see [our AI compliance case study](/case-studies/ai-compliance-scoring-platform).", "q": "How is compliance handled across jurisdictions?"}, {"a": "Multi-rail routing with automatic failover and idempotent settlement, so a single provider outage never halts the business.", "q": "How do you reduce settlement risk?"}, {"a": "Primarily [enterprise software](/services/enterprise-software), [automation](/services/automation), and [AI solutions](/services/ai-solutions).", "q": "Which services apply to finance?"}], "kind": "industry", "solutions": ["A double-entry ledger as the financial source of truth", "AI-driven sanctions and risk screening in real time", "Multi-rail, idempotent settlement with failover", "Hybrid rules-plus-ML fraud detection"], "challenges": ["Money movement that must always reconcile", "Real-time compliance across many jurisdictions", "Settlement latency and single-rail fragility", "Fraud at scale without blocking good customers"], "internalLinks": [{"href": "/platform", "anchor": "Baalvion Operating System"}, {"href": "/case-studies/real-time-cross-border-settlement", "anchor": "real-time cross-border settlement"}, {"href": "/news/finance/trade-finance-automation", "anchor": "trade finance automation"}, {"href": "/services/enterprise-software", "anchor": "enterprise software"}]}, "contentBlocks": [{"id": "blk-0", "type": "heading", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "Sector Overview", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-1", "type": "paragraph", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "Finance is the sector Baalvion knows most intimately — the [Baalvion Operating System](/platform) was built to move value across 198 markets. Financial systems have an unforgiving requirement: the money must always reconcile, every decision must be defensible, and nothing can be lost. We engineer to that bar."}}, {"id": "blk-2", "type": "heading", "order": 2, "content": {"text": "Challenges", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-3", "type": "html", "order": 3, "content": {"html": "<ul><li><strong>Integrity:</strong> every movement must balance and reconcile, always.</li><li><strong>Compliance:</strong> sanctions and KYC/AML screening across many jurisdictions, in real time.</li><li><strong>Settlement:</strong> latency and reliance on a single rail create risk.</li><li><strong>Fraud:</strong> stopping it without blocking legitimate customers.</li></ul>"}}, {"id": "blk-4", "type": "heading", "order": 4, "content": {"text": "How Baalvion Helps", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-5", "type": "paragraph", "order": 5, "content": {"text": "We build on a double-entry ledger so every transaction balances, add real-time AI compliance screening as in [AI compliance scoring across 180+ jurisdictions](/case-studies/ai-compliance-scoring-platform), settle across multiple rails with idempotency and failover as in [real-time cross-border settlement](/case-studies/real-time-cross-border-settlement), and detect fraud with the hybrid engine from our [fraud detection](/case-studies/fraud-detection-engine) work."}}, {"id": "blk-6", "type": "heading", "order": 6, "content": {"text": "Relevant Services", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-7", "type": "paragraph", "order": 7, "content": {"text": "Finance engagements draw on [enterprise software](/services/enterprise-software), [automation](/services/automation), and [AI solutions](/services/ai-solutions), with the strategy explored in [trade finance automation](/news/finance/trade-finance-automation) and [cross-border compliance AI](/news/finance/cross-border-compliance-ai)."}}, {"id": "blk-8", "type": "heading", "order": 8, "content": {"text": "Outcomes", "level": 2}}, {"id": "blk-9", "type": "paragraph", "order": 9, "content": {"text": "Finance platforms that reconcile to the cent, clear faster across borders, screen every transaction in real time with auditable decisions, and stop more fraud while blocking fewer good customers."}}]}	67	State changed to published	2026-06-11 12:31:30.21+00
4e93ff6c-cb79-4375-a921-ce5628a7b323	f16f4b4d-7b5f-4ae5-85fc-9971acbf0984	1	The Art of Acquiring a Heritage Timepiece	{"slug": "guide-heritage-timepiece", "title": "The Art of Acquiring a Heritage Timepiece", "status": "published", "tagIds": [], "excerpt": "What separates a watch from a horological investment.", "seoMetadata": {"title": "The Art of Acquiring a Heritage Timepiece", "description": "What separates a watch from a horological investment."}, "customFields": {"date": "2024-03-14", "kind": "buying-guide", "tips": ["Originality of dial, hands and movement is paramount — service parts erode value.", "Box, papers and service history complete the provenance.", "Complications and limited production drive long-term desirability."], "author": "Marcus Aurelius", "category": "Artisanal", "targetKeyword": "luxury watch investment guide", "investmentOutlook": "Complicated, limited-production references from established houses hold value best."}, "contentBlocks": [{"id": "blk-0", "type": "paragraph", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "A heritage timepiece is measured in generations, not seasons. Originality is the single greatest determinant of value."}}, {"id": "blk-1", "type": "paragraph", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "Full box, papers and an unbroken service history can add materially to a reference’s worth."}}]}	67	State changed to published	2026-06-10 19:08:01.522+00
2a5f1402-3585-4a76-ba3a-d3a77c7aa935	6822c2a6-661c-4f0b-b331-3305e76814c3	1	The Architecture of Time	{"slug": "ed-architecture-of-time", "title": "The Architecture of Time", "status": "published", "tagIds": [], "excerpt": "An exploration of horological investment within the global Maison context.", "seoMetadata": {"title": "The Architecture of Time | AMARISÉ Journal", "description": "Discover the expert perspective on luxury watch investment at Maison Amarisé."}, "customFields": {"date": "2024-03-01", "kind": "editorial", "author": "Elena Vance", "category": "Artisanal", "targetKeyword": "luxury watch investment"}, "contentBlocks": [{"id": "blk-0", "type": "paragraph", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "In the heart of our ateliers, the pursuit of horological perfection remains a dialogue between human brilliance and timeless heritage."}}, {"id": "blk-1", "type": "paragraph", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "The standard of the absolute is never compromised — every complication earns its place."}}]}	67	State changed to published	2026-06-10 19:08:01.543+00
ba9998ce-abf8-4856-957f-16e79af4f34a	f08f1841-b4b7-4bcf-8eb8-f9467d679e11	1	Haute Couture: A Human Dialogue	{"slug": "ed-haute-couture-dialogue", "title": "Haute Couture: A Human Dialogue", "status": "published", "tagIds": [], "excerpt": "Bespoke couture as a conversation between maker and wearer.", "seoMetadata": {"title": "Haute Couture: A Human Dialogue | AMARISÉ Journal", "description": "Bespoke couture trends from the senior curators at Maison Amarisé."}, "customFields": {"date": "2024-03-04", "kind": "editorial", "author": "Elena Vance", "category": "Seasonal", "targetKeyword": "bespoke couture trends"}, "contentBlocks": [{"id": "blk-0", "type": "paragraph", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "Couture is the slowest of luxuries — measured in fittings, not in minutes."}}, {"id": "blk-1", "type": "paragraph", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "Each garment is a record of the hours and the hands that made it."}}]}	67	State changed to published	2026-06-10 19:08:01.559+00
2eb96342-51fa-4197-aeb7-d9b4ae0f92cb	62d01791-7e6b-4d42-af89-a99fdd8c8e8e	1	The Soul of Silk	{"slug": "ed-soul-of-silk", "title": "The Soul of Silk", "status": "published", "tagIds": [], "excerpt": "Heritage silk craft and the archives that preserve it.", "seoMetadata": {"title": "The Soul of Silk | AMARISÉ Journal", "description": "Heritage silk craft at Maison Amarisé."}, "customFields": {"date": "2024-03-07", "kind": "editorial", "author": "Elena Vance", "category": "Artisanal", "targetKeyword": "heritage silk craft"}, "contentBlocks": [{"id": "blk-0", "type": "paragraph", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "Hand-painted archives carry the memory of every artisan who touched them."}}, {"id": "blk-1", "type": "paragraph", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "Silk is the maison’s quietest material and its most expressive."}}]}	67	State changed to published	2026-06-10 19:08:01.579+00
3c45f61b-737b-4467-ab4c-a8f0ad59709e	beb703c4-210b-449d-9933-fc9c2be97d98	1	Opaque Brilliance: Diamonds of the Future	{"slug": "ed-opaque-brilliance", "title": "Opaque Brilliance: Diamonds of the Future", "status": "published", "tagIds": [], "excerpt": "On rare diamond collecting and the long horizon of value.", "seoMetadata": {"title": "Opaque Brilliance | AMARISÉ Journal", "description": "Rare diamond collecting at Maison Amarisé."}, "customFields": {"date": "2024-03-10", "kind": "editorial", "author": "Elena Vance", "category": "Artisanal", "targetKeyword": "rare diamond collecting"}, "contentBlocks": [{"id": "blk-0", "type": "paragraph", "order": 0, "content": {"text": "The rarest stones are bought not for a season but for a lineage."}}, {"id": "blk-1", "type": "paragraph", "order": 1, "content": {"text": "Certification and provenance turn brilliance into permanence."}}]}	67	State changed to published	2026-06-10 19:08:01.593+00
